save_path_categories(25.10)                        save_path_categories(25.10)

Name
       save_path_categories - Saves the selected categories in a path category
       file

Syntax
       save_path_categories

       [-help]

       -filename <filename>

       Saves the selected categories in a path category file. Use the category
       file  to load the saved category definitions in a new timing debug ses-
       sion. To load the saved category definitions, use  the  load_path_cate-
       gories command.

       For  more information, see the Debugging Timing Results chapter of User
       Guide.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information for each save_path_categories parameter.

              For  a  detailed  description of the command and all its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man save_path_categories

       -filename <filename>
              Specifies the name of the saved category file.

Example
       The following command saves the path category file category.cat:

       save_path_categories -filename category.cat

Related Information
       The Timing Budgeting chapter of the Innovus User Guide document.

